ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's great if you do your project with a professor you love working with.

if you're looking at evaluations deciding whether to take this class before you're a senior: yeah, why not? just find an advisor you want to work with and a project you want to work on, if that's more appealing to you than taking a class, go for it! workload is ~10 hours of lab per week. you'll have to write a midterm report, a final 15-page paper, and give a presentation. that's it
